import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['precipitation', 'location'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['location'] == loc]['precipitation'] for loc in data['location'].unique()], 
               labels=data['location'].unique())
    ax.set_xlabel('Location')
    ax.set_ylabel('Precipitation')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of precipitation across different locations?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'], label='Max Temperature')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['temp_min'], label='Min Temperature')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')
    ax.set_title('How does temperature vary over time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['wind'], data['temp_max'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['temp_max'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean temp_max: {data['temp_max'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(x=data['wind'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean wind: {data['wind'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Wind')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temp_max')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between wind and temperature?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['weather'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red'])
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Condition')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
